hat=E2=80=99s where you want to be. There are three kinds of places you can=
 spend time:=C2=A0
Those without a purpose=C2=A0
Those with an established, fixed purpose=C2=A0
Those that are discovering their purpose.=C2=A0
You tell me which sounds most fun.=C2=A0
I=E2=80=99m going to start using that instead of, =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re so=
 early!=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
For a lot of people, =E2=80=9CDiscovering its purpose=E2=80=9D means findin=
g =E2=80=9CReal use cases.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
To that end, Shopify is one of the more interesting places in tradtech from=
 a crypto perspective =E2=80=93 crypto and commerce are very linked, your C=
EO Tobi [ https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEuKxDAMRE_TXgb_J1l4MZu5hvFH=
nTad2MFWpsntx0kWA0JCiKL0KjiEudTDbKUhOZvFYwOT4dMWQIRK9gbVpmiY5qNQciLRyMhGNZL=
U7LMCrC4tBusOZNv9koLDVPKloJQr8jIOotfRizhRJikXQvqROS9Y8Gp0oG5ft8cEOYCBX6hHyU=
AW80Lc2kN8P_hPL_yk86MhlPXcik8kGU45p4pyxtWX0oMYAuea-ifIiXkdmHtIus58aLtv6ML7V=
JNqckFfaspzP79fboXlOnQC2-e654SHhez8AvGGwzujC9fOkKH27KJ12JNRTE6aT6wD3jCdXgmm=
Jj5q0p1j6ar8b_oHPlN-hw ] seems genuinely interested in it, and there are ov=
er 1 million businesses running on Shopify. Given its size and reach, it fe=
els like Shopify can lend its legitimacy to use cases i.e. if Shopify suppo=
rts something, it is a real use case because Shopify supports it.=C2=A0
With great power comes great responsibility. How did you start approaching =
whether to get involved and what to do in the space?=C2=A0
I guess I=E2=80=99d say, =E2=80=9CGradually and then suddenly?=E2=80=9D I j=
oined Shopify two years ago and found this funny juxtaposition, which was, =
1) a lot of people scattered around the company who were all quite crypto-f=
luent and really knew what they were talking about, but also 2) no driving =
force to align on what to do, aside from payments. Shopify merchants have b=
een able to accept crypto payments for several years now, thanks to third-p=
arty app developers building payment gateways (we are the platform on which=
 commerce is built!).=C2=A0
But then last year when NFTs took off, it really lit a fire under us to go =
find an answer to that question: is this a part of =E2=80=9Cthe best versio=
n of the internet,=E2=80=9D that our platform must offer to merchants? And =
the answer was clearly yes, although it took us a minute to discover why.=
=C2=A0
Indeed. The first crypto news out of the company was, I think, the Chicago =
Bulls NFT store. And when I thought about Shopify=E2=80=99s role starting t=
here, I thought your big push into the space would be something along those=
 lines but richer =E2=80=93 NFT minting, drops, sales. You help businesses =
sell things =E2=80=93 physical and digital - so help them sell sweet, sweet=
 high-margin NFTs. That=E2=80=99s not the way you went. Why?=C2=A0
Well, Packy, that=E2=80=99s the money question I want to talk to you about.=
 (Although I=E2=80=99d be remiss if I didn=E2=80=99t mention that you can s=
ell NFTs on Shopify, head here [ https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2Kh=
DAQhJ9mcpT8jx5y2Mu-Roixo2E0kaRd8e034ywsNN3QRVF85R3CnMtl9lyRvJfFaweT4KwrIEIh=
R4Vi42SY5r1QciCTkRPrVU9itaEAbC6uBssBZD_GNXqHMafbQSlXZDFP0YcQnBdKSCZH3atnYJI=
BG6iWXLBPrjumCMmDgR8oV05AVrMg7vUhvh78u815nl1d8h7D1fm8tU8KSKLhlHOqKGdcPZXuRO=
c513QMIAc2as_cQ9Jt5l09xorOv95mUkzKOOYS09zk1-I2WG-hQdh2tyNFvCwkN64wffjwU9NNb=
GdIUFp9k3XYylFMDpoPjemPpxWgBFMD7zVpyVNurvQf-gvMR36e ].) But back to our top=
ic: instead of giving you a simple answer (=E2=80=9CBecause we think tokeng=
ated commerce is a 100x bigger opportunity than anyone else realizes, and i=
t=E2=80=99s more inherently interesting to us than anything else=E2=80=9D),=
 I=E2=80=99m gonna give you a newsletter-length answer, cause that=E2=80=99=
s why we=E2=80=99re here, right?=C2=A0
Anyway, let me start my answer with a question for you. It=E2=80=99s a very=
 big question. You ready? Here it is:
When you make a bet on crypto, what is it you=E2=80=99re betting on?=C2=A0
Oooo good one. This answer changes for me, but here=E2=80=99s my current th=
inking.=C2=A0
There was a line in that big Jonathan Haidt article [ https://email.mg2.sub=
stack.com/c/eJxFkUFuxCAMRU8z7CYCEmhYsOim14gMuAkqgRGQjtLT1zNTqRKyvzDW_3p46Li=
WetpbaZ09ytLPG9qM95awd6zsaFiXGKzQch7VZFiwUxCzmllsy2dF3CEm2-uB7Ha4FD30WPJzg3=
Op2GZBaHCIXKPXwo9STpwbKWYhMRg3iZcvHCFi9mjxG-tZMrJkt95v7TK-X-QHnfv9PvQNoSfIP=
frBl51ud1jhJ2YkCdVv8fuhJJeSGldUWvER0nXHEOEacC--gj-vlLj1q6NkiR5paUZtSLBoH8tc=
cSmkelN6GAcvpebuEycjnPYCLhPfVzm0w7UO_usRhFWbS3elxrzS-GuDHdNzQFAW6vuRYz8XzOA=
Shhev_sL-JLismLHSd4QFOsFWYjIUShj-x4eAqlEoI2fNyDkU2sr_pr-NkpjC ] a couple we=
eks ago that immediately made me think of crypto: =E2=80=9CThere is a direc=
tion to history and it is toward cooperation at larger scales.=E2=80=9D Cry=
pto is a bet on cooperation at larger scales without needing to pay compani=
es to sit in the middle and coordinate everything. What do you think?=C2=A0
I specifically like the =E2=80=9Ccoordination=E2=80=9D part of this answer;=
 let=E2=80=99s bookmark that idea. And for the record, I don=E2=80=99t thin=
k there=E2=80=99s one correct answer for this, of course - there are lots o=
f different communities and schools of thought around what blockchains and =
cryptocurrency are here to do for us. That=E2=80=99s a good thing. But I=E2=
=80=99ll tell you mine, which I think covers a lot of what=E2=80=99s import=
ant.
When we bet on crypto =E2=80=9Chappening=E2=80=9D, we=E2=80=99re betting on=
 two things:=20
Wallets change how people behave,=C2=A0
And:
Over time, this behaviour will win.=C2=A0
Since you=E2=80=99re my guest here, I=E2=80=99m going to let you go with al=
l the extra =E2=80=9Cu=E2=80=9D=E2=80=99s. Behaviour. Classy. But yes, I li=
ke this answer because it incorporates both the social and the technical, a=
nd how computers and people interact. =E2=80=9CFirst we shape our interface=
s, and then our interfaces shape us.=E2=80=9D
I think it covers it kinda nicely, don=E2=80=99t you think? It gives someth=
ing for everyone. There=E2=80=99s something for the Sound Money folks (our =
wallets and cryptographic key pairs change the behaviour of how we save and=
 spend, and that behaviour in the long run will outcompete the old behaviou=
r), there=E2=80=99s something for the dapp builders (wallets change how peo=
ple create and consume software), there=E2=80=99s something for communities=
 (wallets change how people collect and present pieces of their identity).=
=C2=A0
I like this starting point because it brings us together on something we ca=
n all agree on. Crypto is fundamentally a kind of behaviour, just as much o=
r arguably even more than it is a kind of technology.=C2=A0
There are many facets to this behaviour, but it starts from cryptography; a=
nd it starts in our wallets, when we sign something. And it starts at one m=
oment, and that=E2=80=99s the magic moment where our wallets open a door in=
to a new world and we step inside.
We=E2=80=99re working on some cool stuff inside that world. We call it toke=
ngated commerce.=C2=A0
To learn what tokengated commerce is, people with wallets can do, how  NFTs=
 let people fit in & stand out, what it means that Shopify is becoming wall=
et-aware, and why all of this needs a blockchain=E2=80=A6
